caption: Far out and unique. I absolutely loved finding this hidden special museum. I am not even a doll collector but I found this collection impressive. Every doll you can imagine from around the world arranged in this little jewel box of a museum. If you are looking for the unusual, you have found it here.

Used to go here when I was an Au Pair. The kids loved it, both girls and boys. Great and well organised exhibition, amazing selection and details about the dools and their making. Trip back in time assured! :)
This place is great! So many dolls of different types. I don't understand why there are not other languages other than French posted. One star off because of that. Check it out though!
All descriptions are in french only, so you can just enjoy looking the dolls, but with the feeling that you wish you can understand something...
I went to the museum this morning but it has been closed since September.  There is no further information on the re-opening date.
I would have appreciated an English translation as well. Perhaps next time I go to Paris?
Small private doll museum for doll lovers.

Sad it's closing
Museum created in 1994, presented a collection of dolls from the 1800s to 1959. This museum permanently closed its doors in 2017.

Although there are only six rooms, four of which are permanent and two exhibitions, it is already a paradise for doll lovers! The museum offers a chronological view of European dolls. I was surprised to see dolls there that looked like Asians. And these dolls are really different from the Chinese dolls which are less realistic.

you thought you were old enough to play dolls. well go to the doll museum (a bit hidden in a dead end) to understand the importance of the doll for growing up well. a shop attached to the museum allows you to have your most beautiful dolls repaired (it's priceless to keep).

I found this museum accidentally as I was going to visit The Anne Frank Garden. It was a wonderful accident as it is beautiful to visit. Although I am a man, as a child I always played with dolls and I have a special love for them. A visit to this magical place is highly recommended.-

This upcoming closure is truly heartbreaking. Through the evolution of dolls, we revisit the history of France from 1870 to today. We immerse ourselves in our memories and delight in the wonder of the 5-year-old girl who holds your hand.

A cute little museum next to the Forum des Halles, you can wander around for an hour with the multiple wax and porcelain figures; we go back to childhood, we relive our little girl's dreams and we wander the aisles. On the other hand, the entrance is a little expensive.

It's a scam. The bisque doll shown in the photo is from the shop next door, and the museum is filled with dolls in ethnic costumes from all over the world. If you are expecting bisque dolls or dollhouses, you will be disappointed. In the notebooks of the visitors, they wrote the same thing in Japanese as I wrote here.
A return to childhood that we must preserve. We cannot remain indifferent, fortunately this museum exists. Thank you
This museum will close permanently in a few days. .to see one last time if you like dolls. .old and newer
It's really a mini museum, we did the tour in 5 minutes, it's too expensive for what it is. Museum is a big word
Unfortunately closed since mid-September 2017, a small museum rich in the collection of the Odin brothers, a stone's throw from the Center Pompidou in Paris
It's not crazy. Unless you are a doll enthusiast. Sometimes nice events, second-hand fabrics for example
You have to love dolls. It seems obvious but I went there thinking that the museum would give me a taste for these things but no...
Very good and a shame that the museum has permanently closed its doors
Not the biggest museum in Paris but rather nice.
Because they are all gorgeous they seem real. and they make me remember my little dolls
very very cute classic and very trashy barbie dolls chubby dolls with blue eyes and red curls school objects
A more than complete collection on the evolution of this toy. A private museum to discover
Very beautiful museum, too bad it had to close...
Too bad this place will close its doors at the beginning of September
What I liked best: the store! There are some lovely treasures to be found there!
Cool place for those who want to go back in time.
